  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting conflict sensitive implementation of the Building Bridges to Unity Initiative (BBI)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">#N/A</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The expected outcomes that will contribute to this objective are: 1. Increased capacity and coordination among peace actors in Kenya to identify and mitigate conflict risks and polarisations resulting from the progress and implementation of the BBI 2. Increased understanding among key stakeholders (including civil society, county and national government and development partners) on the conflict risks of the BBI and increasing willingness to take mitigation measures.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of this project is to increase the inclusiveness of the Building Bridges for Unity Initiative to reduce the risk of violent conflict as Kenya moves towards elections in 2022</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will support peace actors across Kenya to analyse and begin to address the incipient risks of violent conflict occasioned by tensions over the Building Bridges for Unity Initiative.</narrative>
  </description>
